
Step 1: Create ECR repository
Go AWS Console:
Search:
ECR
Open:
Amazon Elastic Container Registry
Click:
Create repository
Repository name:
myweb
Visibility:
Choose:
Private

Create repository

After creation AWS gives repository URI like:

385105852201.dkr.ecr.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com/myweb

Important: save this URI.

Step 2: Login Docker to ECR

Inside EC2 run:

aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | docker login --username AWS

--password-stdin your-repository-uri-without-/myweb

If aws command fails
Install AWS CLI first:
sudo yum install aws-cli -y
Check:
aws --version

If AWS credentials not configured
Run:
aws configure
Enter:
 Access key
 Secret key
 region = ap-south-1

Step 3: Tag your image
Your current image:
myweb:v1
ECR requires full repository name.
Run:
docker tag myweb:v1 your-full-ecr-uri:latest
Example:
docker tag myweb:v1 123456789012.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/myweb:latest



Step 4: Push image
Run:
docker push your-full-ecr-uri:latest

Example:
docker push 123456789012.dkr.ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/myweb:latest


Step 5: Verify in AWS Console

Refresh ECR repository.

You should see:

latest

Image uploaded successfully
